4. The Isgur-Wise form factors and comparison with Bjorken sum rule constraints

Due to the heavy spin symmetry, matrix elements of weak heavy quark currents _Qv\Gamma Qv0 in the heavy quark limit can be parametrized by means of a few unique form factors (Isgur-Wise functions) depending on the velocity transfer (v \Delta v0) [14]

A(v \Delta v0) _Tv\Gamma Tv0 ; (53) G(v \Delta v0) _S_v \Gamma Tv0 v0_ + h:c: ; (54)\Phi

